This needs more logic in it.  what if finalResponse is 500, and subResponse is 200?  The 500 will get overridden, right?

we probably need to handle it something to the effect of.

If (subresponse.resultInt() > finalResponse.resultInt){
   finalResponse.resultInt(subResponse.resultInt);
}

now, I'm not sure > is the right operator above, we might need an explicit list of "X error is greater than Y error".  For example, 401 might be higher than 404.
